5. Additional Uses of Information
In addition to the purposes described above, we may use your information to:
Diagnose and fix technical issues with our Services;
Enforce our Terms of Service;
Comply with legal obligations and respond to lawful requests; and
Conduct research and business analysis by using aggregated, non-identifiable data.
6. Sharing and Disclosure of Information
We do not sell your personal information. However, we may share your information under the following
        circumstances:
Service Providers
: We work with trusted service providers to process payments, fulfill
          orders, deliver advertisements, and perform analytics. These providers only use your data as instructed by us.
Legal and Safety
: We may share information to comply with legal obligations, enforce our
          rights, prevent fraud, and protect the safety of our users.
Business Transfers
: In the event of a merger, acquisition, or asset sale, we may transfer
          your information to the new entity, which will be subject to this Policy.
Aggregated Information
: We may share anonymized, non-personally identifiable data for general
          business purposes.
7. Data Retention
We retain your information as long as needed to provide Services, comply with legal requirements, and fulfill
        the purposes described in this Policy. If you wish to delete your information, please contact us at
        admin@kuddl.com. We will delete your data unless retention is required for legal purposes.
8. Security of Your Information
We implement technical and administrative security measures to protect your personal information from
        unauthorized access, alteration, and disclosure. However, no system is entirely secure, and we cannot guarantee
        absolute protection.
9. Children's Privacy
Our Services are intended for general audiences and not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly
        collect information from children under 13 without parental consent. If we become aware of such collection, we
        will delete the information. Contact us at admin@kuddl.com if you believe we may have collected a minor's
        information without consent.
10. International Data Transfers
To provide our Services, your information may be transferred to and processed in countries outside the U.S.,
        including the European Union. By using our Services, you consent to these data transfers in accordance with
        applicable law.
11. “Do Not Track” Signals
Our Services do not respond to “Do Not Track” browser settings. You may still adjust your browser settings to
        manage cookies and tracking technologies.
12. California Privacy Rights
Under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), California residents have specific rights regarding their
        personal information, including the right to:
Request access to the categories or specific pieces of information we collect;
Request deletion of personal information;
Opt out of “sales” of personal information (although we do not sell your information); and
Not face discrimination for exercising CCPA rights.
California residents may make requests regarding these rights by contacting us at admin@kuddl.com. We will
        verify your request using information associated with your account.
13. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. Any updates
        will be posted on our website, and continued use of our Services constitutes acceptance of the revised Policy.
